help i think i am dying of food poisoining i have back ache aswell how do i rest food poisoning treatment self care at home short episodes of vomiting and small amounts of diarrhea lasting less than hours can usually be cared for at home do not eat solid food while nauseous or vomiting but drink plenty of fluids small frequent sips of clear liquids those you can see through are the best way to stay hydrated avoid alcoholic caffeinated or sugary drinks if possible over the counter rehydration products made for children such as pedialyte and rehydralyte are expensive but good to use if available sports drinks such as gatorade and powerade are fine for adults if they are diluted with water because at full strength they contain too much sugar which can worsen diarrhea after successfully tolerating fluids eating should begin slowly when nausea and vomiting have stopped plain foods that are easy on the stomach should be started in small amounts consider eating rice wheat breads potatoes cereals low sugar cereals lean meats and chicken not fried to start milk can be given safely although some people may experience additional stomach upset due to lactose intolerance most food poisonings do not require the use of over the counter medicines to stop diarrhea but they are generally safe if used as directed it is not recommended that these medications be given to children if there is a question or concern you should always check with your doctor Stomach cancer Fecal incontinence Food Chocolate Breastfeeding Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Lactose intolerance Crohn's disease Coeliac disease Veganism Hypoglycemia Rehydration Dehydration Milk Vegetarianism Atkins Nutritional Approach Breakfast Prostate cancer Folic acid Food allergy Adjustable gastric band Gastroparesis Hangover Gastroesophageal reflux disease Paracetamol Guinea pig Dietary fiber Breakfast cereal Sulfasalazine Fancy rat Diabetes mellitus Anorexia nervosa German cuisine Gastroenteritis Japanese cuisine Fugu Jewish cuisine Ul